Azure SQL Managed Instance provides a fully managed SQL Server-compatible PaaS with near-100% on-premises compatibility, ideal for enterprise apps balancing performance, availability, and cost. It deploys into a VNet with private connectivity, supporting General Purpose (cost-optimized) and Business Critical (high-performance) tiers. Core app functionality matches across tiers; use Business Critical only for demanding non-functionals like sub-second latency.
​

Service Tiers
General Purpose tier suits typical workloads with flexible scaling; Business Critical adds local SSD for low-latency IO and Always On HA. From a cost view, tier selection drives ~2x difference—reserve Business Critical for RTO<5s needs.
​

Optionality
Options focus on HA/DR and read replicas. Share resources via multi-database instances or schemas for efficiency.

Multiple Instances (1 DB Each)

Ensures CPU/memory isolation.

[-] Instance-level billing.
​

[+] Per-app cost tracking; instance backups.

Single Instance (Multi-DB)

[-] Shared resources; monitor via Query Store.

[-] No DB-granular billing—use Cost Management.
​

[+] Lower cost; DB exports via sqlcmd/BCP; Terraform DB ops.

Context Diagram
Azure SQL MI VNet architecture with Private Endpoint.
​

Networking
Requires /27+ delegated subnet in VNet. Terraform: subnet_id, vnet_name. Private IP only; non-contiguous CIDRs allocated regionally.
​

Connectivity
Control plane: ARM APIs (CLI/Terraform) with SQL MI Contributor RBAC. Instance: Port 1433 via Private Endpoint (TLS 1.2+ enforced). Auth: Entra ID tokens (auto-refresh), service principals—no certs needed. Connectors: Native ADO.NET/JDBC.
​

HA/DR
Zone-redundant Always On (99.99% SLA, RPO=0, auto-failover). DR: Failover groups (sync geo) or geo-restore. Terraform enables via SKU/zone config.
​

Backup/Recovery
Automated geo-redundant backups (7-35 days; PITR to 180 days). Instance-level; Terraform: backup_retention_days.
​

Scalability
vCore scale-up (GP: 80 vCore/16TB; BC: 80 vCore/16TB). Online resize BC; read replicas for scale-out. Max 64TB storage.
​

Tier	Max vCore	Max RAM (GB)	Storage (TB)
GP	80	520	16 
​
BC	80	540	16 
​
Deployment/SDLC
Terraform azurerm_mssql_managed_instance or AVM module in LZ. Plugins: KeyVault (CMEK), Entra, EPA.
​

Patching/Upgrades
Automated weekly (configurable window, <30s BC downtime). In-place major upgrades (SQL 2022/2019 supported).
​

Monitoring/Logging
Azure Monitor/Logs Analytics: errorlogs, audits (SQLSecurityAuditEvents). Splunk integration.
​

Security
Entra RBAC + SQL auth; Private Endpoint mandatory. CMEK via Key Vault (TDE); EKM/Assured Workloads for compliance. No public IPs.
​

Cost Optimization
Right-size vCore; Reservations 30-50% savings; stop DEV instances. HA doubles cost.
​

Guardrails & Lifecycle
Policy-enforced (no public access); prod-ready with LZ.
